Cheyenne Mountain Complex was built in the 1960s to protect the US military in the event of a nuclear war . 
  It was home to the North American Aerospace Command (NORAD) and US Northern Command during the Cold War . 
  The complex was built to withstand a nuclear attack and is protected by a 25-ton blast door . 
  The base is home to more than 1,000 personnel and was the command and control center of NORAD . 
  The military shut down the base in 2006 but has announced it will be used again for advanced tracking and communications equipment . 
 